This is a short description on the use of IDL erl_genserv demo,
compiled via Rebar IDL Compiler plugin. A client asks an unusual 
greeting message from a service that lies on an Erlang-genserver.

Instructions.

    On the command shell type:
    --------------------------

        make                            (generate the code from IDL
                                         definitions and build the app)


    On the erlang shell type :
    --------------------------

        {ok, R} = idlexample_Hello:oe_create(). (initialize the server)

        idlexample_Hello:sayHello(R).   ( ask the greeting message )

        idlexample_Hello:shutdown(R).   ( call the shutdown funciton)

